Geographic distribution.
Hypoponera
is the most cosmopolitan of all ponerine genera, occurring on every continent except Antarctica and extending into many temperate regions. Endemic species are apparently absent from many island groups ( e.g., Polynesia), but several widespread tramp species have become established even in these locations ( Taylor, 1967 ;
Ingram et al. , 2006
).

